reviewText: Goes very fast and you have to keep pausing it define a function is talking about

The title is a little misleading.  This DVD is certainly not what I would call an in depth look at the D810, but rather a summary of all of the programmable aspects of the camera and I don't feel, the title 'Beyond the basics' is appropriate.  Take a day or two and read the manual thoroughly and you'll have the same information.  I once had a DVD for a Sony Z7U and it was absolutely spot on, I had hoped this would be the same, but.......
Very pleased with my purches, would recommend
A totally waist of money to buy this DVD !
